            <font color="white">
                Apollo is an online trading card game (TCG) set in the future.
                Collect cards to build your space armada and defeat your opponent to become the ruler of the star system.
                Build up your fleet with a wide variety of ships, troops, and races as you try to eliminate your opponents forces.

                <h4>Business Background:</h4>
                1.<b>Business: </b>Raven Games is a gaming entertainment company established in 2018 and located in Jacksonville Florida. It is owned by three students at the University of North Florida .<br /><br />
                <div class="b">a) <b>Origin:</b> The three students had initially started Raven Games for class project, but with initial support, decided to continue and create a full-fledged company long after the assignment was completed.</div>
                <div class="b">b) <b>Products: </b>Currently, Apollo is the one and only product offered by Raven Games but that is planned to change in the future. With other games on the horizon, Apollo will not be left behind. All products from Raven Games will be support for years to comes, regardless of player base size.</div><br />
                2.<b>Mission: </b>Raven Games is determined to provide a unique and enjoyable collectable card gaming experience in multiple different ways:<br /><br />
                <div class="b">a)<b>Pricing: </b>Apollo is free to play, allowing people to enjoy endless of hours of entertainment at no cost. We do offer very competitive pricing for extra card packs and story DLC should users want to support the company or expedite their card collection.</div>
                <div class="b">b)<b>Community: </b>Apollo is extremely community focused, down to letting the community decide on future updates and cards for every new feature that comes to the game.</div>
                <div class="b">c)<b>Updates: </b>New features will come swiftly into the game, no waiting months for updates from developers. We experiment along with the community and will not keep updates or balancing changes behind closed doors.</div>
                <div class="b">d)<b>Support: </b>We offer a top tier support system for our users. Responding to all concerns via email within 24 hours.</div><br />
                3.<b>Board Members: </b>The presidents of Raven Games are currently the three college students that originally started the company. Brandon Bradlee, Joseph Betbeze, and Daniel Cassel. Along with co owning the company, the three also advise the company’s branches of Account Services, Creative Services, Marketing and Management.<br /><br />
                4.<b>Tax Policy: </b>Tax pricing varies from state to state in the US, but our pricing does not. If you live in a state with 6% sales tax or 7% sales tax, you will always pay the listed price on the website which will always be the same regardless of your location. Raven Games will take the hit on the sales tax for our customers regardless of where they are from in the US.<br />


