        <h3 style="color:#ffffff">FAQ</h3>
        <p>

            <a name="1"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">What is Apollo?</h4>
                            <font color="white">
                                Apollo is a free to play digital strategy card game.
                                <a name="2"></a>
                                <h4 style="color:#587bff">Do I need to know anything about strategy card games or space technology to know how to play?</h4>
                                Nope! Apollo was designed to be played by anyone regardless of how familiar they are with strategy card games or space technology. The game will teach you as you play.
                                <a name="3"></a>
                                <h4 style="color:#587bff">On which platforms is Apollo available?</h4>
                                Apollo is currently only available on PC systems.
                                <a name="4"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">How do I get my hands on this game?</h4>
                                Click this <a href="">link</a> to download the game.
                                <a name="5"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">How can I play this game on my mobile device?</h4>
                                Currently Apollo is not playable on mobile devices
                                <a name="6"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">Do I need an account to play Apollo?</h4>
                                Yes. In order to play Apollo you must be signed into your Apollo account.
                                <a name="7"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">Why do I need an Apollo Account?</h4>
                                Your account allows us to keep track of what cards you’ve earned, in addition to all your stats as a player. Your Apollo account can also be used for the community forum and in responding to online polls.
                                <a name="8"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">
                                    Do I need an internet connection to play Apollo?
                                </h4>
                                Yes. In order to play Apollo you must be sign into your Apollo account which does require internet access.
                                <a name="9"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">How much are card packs?</h4>
                                1 card pack - $.99<br />
                                2 card pack - $1.99<br />
                                5 card pack - $3.99<br />
                                10 card pack - $5.99<br />
                                25 card pack - $11.99<br />
                                50 card pack - $19.99<br /><br />

                                Story DLC is also available:<br />
                                Rogues Story Expansion - $19.99<br />
                                Android Core Story Expansion - $19.99<br />
                                Enhanced Humans Expansion - $19.99<br /><br />
                                <a href="http://localhost:65225/Product/List/?Page=1">Purchase card packs now</a>
                                <a name="10"></a><h4 style="color:#587bff">
                                    Can I refund a card pack?
                                </h4>
                                Unfortunately, with the nature of our game we cannot allow returns for any purchases. Our card packs are randomized and set upon purchase. Were we to allow returns it could open a door for people to be able to see what they got in packs and then return them if they did not contain exactly what they wanted. The same goes for our story DLCs which earn the player packs and special cards during their playthrough.
